1. Basic Copyright Statement
All source code, design documents, architectural theories, algorithm logic, and derivative works of the Environmental Computation (EC) project are original intellectual property independently developed by the project creator.

2. Development Phase Restrictions (Current Valid Period)
During the ongoing research, design, and iterative development stage of the project:
2.1 Any form of commercial use is strictly prohibited, including but not limited to paid services, commercial embedding, product sales, and profit-oriented secondary development.
2.2 Unauthorized copying, full or partial duplication, external dissemination, sharing, or distribution of any project files is forbidden.
2.3 Academic reference, experimental verification, and research citation are permitted only with complete and explicit source attribution. Any citation must clearly indicate the original project affiliation; concealed quotation or disguised plagiarism is not allowed.

3. Formal Release & Open Source Rules (Subsequent Effective Period)
Upon the project’s overall completion and official release, partial open-source authorization will be activated. The following permanent restrictions shall always be observed:
3.1 Commercial application is permitted, provided clear and prominent source attribution is retained in project interfaces, documentation, and public introductions.
3.2 No individual or organization may delete, modify, or conceal original copyright marks or source identification information.
3.3 Unauthorized plagiarism, tampering, rebranding, or disguised copying of core designs, protocol rules, and core algorithms is strictly prohibited.

4. Liability Explanation
Any violation of the above provisions constitutes infringement of the original intellectual property rights. The project creator reserves the right to pursue legal liability and claim compensation for all infringements.
Access, browsing, or temporary use of project files does not imply any implicit authorization. All usage rights are granted solely under the terms of this license.
